news.title: China Evergrande Group debt revamp plan fails to cheer investors
news.para: Evergrande is the world's most indebted developer with around $300 billion in liabilities. Its offshore debt restructuring, the country's biggest such exercise, is aimed at saving it from a disorderly collapse.

news.title: Average long-term US mortgage rate falls to 6.42% this week
news.para: Mortgage buyer Freddie Mac reported Thursday that the average on the benchmark 30-year rate fell to 6.42% from 6.6% last week. The average rate a year ago was 4.42%.

news.title: Haryana: Panel seeks report from town planners over ban on four-floor buildings
news.para: The letter was sent on Wednesday. On February 23, the Haryana government decided to temporarily suspend all fresh building plan approvals for stilt plus four floors across the state.

news.title: Government offices, institutes pay tax dues in Sambhajinagar
news.para: In the latest recovery drive, the Food and Drugs Administration (FDA) on Tuesday paid Rs 19 lakh it owed towards property tax dues.

news.title: Saran DM distributes land papers to 194 landless people
news.para: Earlier, the DM greeted people with good wishes on this historical day, and said "This state would touch the height of progress with feelings of unity, brotherhood, social equality and good will."

news.title: Ludhiana civic body buildings yet to adopt rain water harvesting
news.para: Civic officials have been framing proposals for over a decade to install RWH in their zonal buildings, but till date nothing concrete has been done.

news.title: Government to grant title for dotted lands, Andhra Pradesh House clears bill
news.para: Thousands of farmers across the state are eagerly looking for the implementation of the new law for the resolution of dotted (prohibited) land controversy.

news.title: Kolkata: Sec V land hurdle for airport metro
news.para: This land currently has a tower that was earlier used to guide aircraft to land. AAI has agreed to part with the land, but only on a 30-year lease.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body to serve notices to owners of old buildings
news.para: The officials of GVMC initially identified 320 structures in the year 2016. Later, the number increased to 450 in the GVMC limits.

news.title: Safety certification in place, but verification still lacking in Delhi
news.para: An official of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi said the notification of Unified Building Bylaws, 2001, and National Building Code has boosted compliance with norms.

news.title: Chalet Hotels acquires an 80-room resort in Khandala
news.para: ​The resort land is owned by Sonmil Industries Pvt Ltd, while the hotel structure and its business are owned by The Dukes Retreat Pvt Ltd.

news.title: BHIVE Workspace starts new co-working centre with 5,000 desks in Bengaluru
news.para: The co-working centre, developed in collaboration with the Garuda Group, is spread over 2 lakh square feet and will offer over 5,000 seats.

news.title: DDA warns public about fake URL being used in the name of its housing scheme
news.para: ​In a statement, the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) said it has has taken a serious view in this matter, and complaints have been lodged in the Economic Offences Wing and Cyber Crime cell of the Delhi Police.

news.title: GST tribunal, InVITs among likely 60 changes to Finance Bill
news.para: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman is expected to move around 60 changes to the Finance Bill, 2023 when it is taken up for passage in the Lok Sabha. These will include clarifications and also measures to take the sting out of some of the tax proposals announced in the budget.

news.title: Decision on NA tax exclusion in budget session in Maharashtra: Revenue minister
news.para: "We are considering the request from federations and members and a report has been readied by the revenue department after taking the opinion of all stakeholders. We would come out with a final decision at the end of the assembly session," said the minister.
